The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for solving design challenges in heterogeneous ultra-dense networks (H-UDNs), which are networks with high density and diversity of network entities. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on utilizing graphical representations of H-UDNs to design efficient machine learning algorithms, which involves both graph theory and machine learning techniques, making categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), systems and control (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) likely as well.
